We should be protecting and expanding health care—not gutting it.

This fight isn’t over. #ProtectOurCare #CoveredCA
California and Democrats have worked hard to expand access to affordable care. This bill would rip that progress apart—harming families, seniors, and young people alike.

This isn’t about saving money. It’s about making it harder for families to access care.

More red tape. Higher costs. Fewer people insured. That’s the goal of this bill.

A 45-year-old individual making $60,000?

You could see a hike of $1,245 more a year in premiums. That’s money working families just don’t have.

A family of four making $125,000?

Expect your premiums to go up by more than $7,000 a year—for the same coverage.

A 60-year-old couple making $82,000?

Your premiums could nearly quadruple—jumping from an average of $6,970 to over $26,000 a year.
If you make $60,000 or less, get ready to pay an extra $200/month just to keep your health insurance. That’s nearly $2,400 more a year—for basic coverage.

Republicans’ Big Ugly Bill is a direct attack on affordable health care.

It forces 2 million people on Covered California to cut through more red tape and pay more—or lose coverage entirely. 🧵

60 years after Medicare & Medicaid became law, Trump gutted them.

His Big, Ugly Bill will strip health care from 15M people—2.3M in California. 28 rural hospitals will shut down.

This is a betrayal of working families. We’re fighting to stop these cuts and save your care.
